description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Assessor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Mental Health Nurse/Allied Health Professional&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the expansion and development of the skill mix in our team, we are able to offer the following opportunity for a motivated Registered Mental Health Nurse or Allied Health Professional with mental experience wishing to develop their career working within a Clinical Commissioning Group. The role is working in the Specialist Assessment and Placements Team based in Gravesend, Kent. You will be employed by NHS Kent and Medway CCG, though the team provide a service to those clients residing predominantly within the Medway, Swale and Dartford, Gravesham and Swanley area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Specialist Assessment and Placements Team is responsible for undertaking detailed clinical assessments, quality reviews and commissioning services and support for individuals subject to various NHS eligibility criteria, such as The National Framework for NHS Continuing Healthcare and NHS Funded Nursing Care and The Mental Health Act, in relation to the commissioning of specialist mental health treatment pathways, Section 117 responsible commissioner pathways and specialist mental health outpatient referrals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Registered Mental Health Nurse or an Allied Health Professional with relevant mental health patient experience and with excellent communication and assessment skills. You will be required to will undertake comprehensive, holistic assessments and reviews of individuals using appropriate assessment tools to implement the National Framework for Continuing Healthcare, Funded Nursing Care and Section 117 aftercare responsibilities. In return we can offer you the opportunity of flexible, varied and interesting work, excellent career progression and the support of a highly motivated, friendly, supportive team and organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours are Monday to Friday 09.00 – 17.00 hours, though we can offer flexibility and part-time or full-time contracts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is important to note that you will need the ability to travel to a variety of locations to undertake this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are based at the Civic Centre, Gravesend and if successful in your application you will be entitled to the 5% outer London Fringe Allowance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits or discussions regarding the posts are warmly welcomed, please contact either:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janice Winter: on 03000 424 999&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: TBC&lt;/p&gt;
